    <section class="content-section" id="how-it-works">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="section-tag">How it works</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Calculating overtime pay</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">The math is simple once you know your state's threshold and multiplier. Here's the full breakdown.</p>

        <div class="two-col">
          <div>
            <div class="steps">
              <div class="step">
                <div class="step-n">1</div>
                <div>
                  <h3>Find your overtime rate</h3>
                  <p>Multiply your regular hourly rate by the overtime multiplier. US federal default is <strong style="color:var(--t1)">1.5× (time and a half)</strong>. Example: $15.00 × 1.5 = $22.50/hr overtime rate.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="step">
                <div class="step-n">2</div>
                <div>
                  <h3>Multiply by overtime hours</h3>
                  <p>Take your overtime rate and multiply by hours worked past the threshold. Example: $22.50/hr × 8 OT hours = <strong style="color:var(--green)">$180 overtime pay</strong>.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="step">
                <div class="step-n">3</div>
                <div>
                  <h3>Add your regular pay</h3>
                  <p>Regular pay = 40 hours × base rate. Add both for your total gross. Example: $600 regular + $180 overtime = <strong style="color:var(--accent)">$780 total</strong>.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="code-block">
              <div class="code-block-header">
                <div class="code-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
                overtime-formula.js
              </div>
              <div class="code-body">
                <code><span class="cm">// 1. Overtime rate</span></code>
                <code>otRate = hourlyRate * multiplier</code>
                <code>&nbsp;</code>
                <code><span class="cm">// 2. Overtime pay</span></code>
                <code>otPay = otRate * otHours</code>
                <code>&nbsp;</code>
                <code><span class="cm">// 3. Total weekly gross</span></code>
                <code>regularPay = hourlyRate * 40</code>
                <code>total = regularPay + otPay</code>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="qualify-card">
              <h3>Who qualifies for overtime?</h3>
              <ul class="qualify-list">
                <li>Hourly workers covered by the FLSA (most US employees)</li>
                <li>Salaried employees earning under $684/week ($35,568/yr)</li>
                <li>Nurses, truck drivers, warehouse, retail, and factory workers</li>
                <li>Part-time workers whose total hours cross the threshold</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
